Return the ball inside
the court. Just relax
and focus on hitting
the ball.

Return the ball into
the orange bar. Watch
your timing, and aim
each shot carefully.

Volley the ball off
the wall and hit the
targets. Controlling
your swing speed and
strength is essential
in aiming your shots.

Watch the ball, and
try to hit it out of
the park. Timing is
everything!

Hit into the target
zones on the field.
Master this, and you'll
be a pro in no time!

The pitcher will keep
throwing those balls,
so focus on making
fast, compact swings!

Drop it in the cup with
a single putt. Check
the lay of the green
by pressing .

Land the ball as close
to the pin as possible.
Practice your stroke
to check the power of
your swing. Hold 
to approach the ball.

Hit the target with
the ball. Before you
take your swing, be
sure to read the
wind direction.

Watch your trainer's
mitts, and try to hit
them. You lose points
if you hit your trainer.

Your trainer throws
ball after ball at you.
Move left and right
to avoid getting hit.

Throw punches at
the punching bags
until you knock them
off their chains.
Well-aimed combo
punches are key.

Knock down the pins
with a single throw.
Twist your wrist to
curve the ball.

Avoid the barriers in
the lane and knock
down the pin. You'll
have to balance speed
and spin.

Knock down as many
pins as you can. A
new row will be added
after each set. Strikes
double your score!

Selecting events that do
not use the Nunchuk.

You can take only one Wii Fitness
test each day. You've already
taken the test today, so please
try again tomorrow.

Wii Fitness

Test your speed, stamina, and
strength to determine your Wii
Fitness Age. Train every day to
lower your Wii Fitness Age.
